tting. Use an adequate sized applicator at last 1\/2 size of pipe diameter Dauber, brush, roller or swab. Apply Christys Primer if required by local code. Uniform Plumbing Code requires the use of a purple primer. CAN BE USED WITHOUT A PRIMER IF LOCAL CODES PERMIT for non-pressure systems up to 6\" and pressure systems below 4\".\u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e2) Apply a full, even coat of cement to the outside of the pipe and a medium coat of cement o inside of the fitting. Coat pipe a second time. Quickly assemble jointly while cement is still fluid on both parts. If dry, pipe and fitting must be re-coated. Push and rotate pipe into the fitting until pipe bottoms in the socket. Hold together until joint sets (approx. 30 seconds).\u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e3) Remove excess cement. Leave joint undisturbed for at least 10 minutes. Full joint strength should be reached within 24 hours depending upon temperature and humidity. See installation Guide for product set and cure time and additional information. STORE BETWEEN 40 °F (4 °C) and 110 °F (43 °C) DO NOT TEST WITH AIR.\u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e \u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003ch4\u003eThis product is not for use in a system using or being tested with compressed air or gases.\u003c\/h4\u003e","brand":"Christys","offers":[{"title":"Default Title","offer_id":39257214517350,"sku":"RH.RHBG.HP 36","price":9.98,"currency_code":"USD","in_stock":true}],"thumbnail_url":"\/\/cdn.shopify.com\/s\/files\/1\/0167\/3543\/6900\/products\/RedHotBlueGlue_Regular_HP-510x600_43e55427-4091-45e1-9f20-a98301c2782f.jpg?v=1592940665"},{"product_id":"arrow-1-4-pt-pool-turf-blue-glue-1132-4","title":"Arrow - 1132-P - Pool \u0026 Turf Blue Glue (Pint)","description":"\u003cp\u003e1132 Pool \u0026amp; Turf is a medium bodied, EXTREMELY fast setting PVC cement for use on all schedules and classes of PVC pipe and fittings up to 6'' diameter with interference fit; Schedule 80 through 4'' diameter.\u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMeets Low-